  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "\n<p><b>Type:</b> Fuinjutsu </p>\n<p><b>Rank:</b> 8 (Spell Level 4)</p>\n<p><b>Chakra Cost:</b> 20</p>\n\n<p><b>Learn DC:</b> 23 | <b>Successes:</b> 6</p>\n<p><b>Perform:</b> 11 | <b>Perform DC:</b> 25</p>\n\n<p><b>Components:</b> C, H, M</p>\n\n<hr>\n\n<p>You bind a target to their blood pact, solidifying their connection to it permanently. The process is painful, and the target suffers 1d6 temporary Strength and Dexterity damage, as well as having to make a save (DC 20) to avoid falling @Condition[unconscious]{unconscious} for 1d6 hours. Once successfully completed, the target can summon creatures of their Blood Pact as though using a Greater Summoning Scroll (see p63). In addition, they can ignore the hand seals component when summoning a creature by increasing the Perform Requirements of the summoning technique by 5.</p>\n\n\n\n",
